64
00:07:16,330 --> 00:07:21,780
You're the one who knows best in the world about how scary the power of a pen is.

65
00:07:21,780 --> 00:07:25,560
It's no fun to provoke someone who holds a pen.

66
00:07:25,560 --> 00:07:26,490
Hey, Jang Hye Mi.

67
00:07:26,490 --> 00:07:31,170
If it goes to trial, make it closed to the public, and I'll be my daughter's attorney.

68
00:07:31,170 --> 00:07:33,590
Pick out a prosecutor in charge for me.

69
00:07:33,590 --> 00:07:34,660
Why don't you get up now?

70
00:07:34,660 --> 00:07:41,710
Gong Ji Cheol, he could be watching you from very close by.

71
00:07:45,930 --> 00:07:52,270
Because even if the body disappears, a wronged soul returns.

72
00:07:52,270 --> 00:07:55,780
Sounds like you've recently joined a religious group.

73
00:08:24,010 --> 00:08:27,960
Big Bro! Who does he think he is?

74
00:08:27,960 --> 00:08:30,500
Are you going to let him put his feet up on the table?

75
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:32,590
Ma Cheol, how old are you?

76
00:08:32,590 --> 00:08:36,430
You know that I'm... 22.

77
00:08:36,430 --> 00:08:39,460
Call him Big Bro from now on.

78
00:08:39,460 --> 00:08:42,460
No, maybe you need to call him your ancestor.

79
00:08:43,530 --> 00:08:44,910
Ancestor?

80
00:08:44,910 --> 00:08:50,260
Jong Beom, since I saved your life, I'm still your Big Bro. Right?

81
00:08:50,260 --> 00:08:51,290
Did you get what I asked?

82
00:08:51,290 --> 00:08:54,280
Hey, you punk! You bastard!

83
00:08:54,280 --> 00:08:56,520
How dare you speak informally?!

84
00:08:56,520 --> 00:09:02,300
Do I need to remove my jacket to prove that I'm a gangster? Where is he looking?

85
00:09:02,300 --> 00:09:04,420
Big Bro, sorry. Let me take my jacket off.

86
00:09:04,420 --> 00:09:06,330
Chang Soon, how old are you?

87
00:09:06,330 --> 00:09:07,990
45, Big Bro.

88
00:09:07,990 --> 00:09:10,200
- You're 45? 
 - Yes.

89
00:09:10,200 --> 00:09:12,500
You can be friends then.

90
00:09:15,130 --> 00:09:20,900
I got the kids to dig it up. Why do you need it?

91
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:28,450
Also, you asked me to find someone for you.

92
00:09:28,450 --> 00:09:32,670
Your stepmother, was it? She doesn't see too well.

93
00:10:03,150 --> 00:10:04,150
 Ms. J states that the novel is fiction based on facts 

94
00:10:04,150 --> 00:10:05,490
 and unrelated to her daughter's case. 

95
00:10:28,430 --> 00:10:33,870
I gave you your last chance, but you threw it away.

96
00:10:33,870 --> 00:10:37,010
Are you saying I'm next after Gong In Woo?

97
00:10:37,010 --> 00:10:39,050
You might be.

98
00:10:40,850 --> 00:10:45,630
I guess you're still angry that I lied to you 30 years ago.

99
00:10:46,750 --> 00:10:53,290
It's funny. Even your biological father betrayed you.

100
00:10:53,290 --> 00:10:57,310
Aren't you pushing it to ask me for goodwill as a human being?

101
00:10:57,310 --> 00:11:01,930
The way you're speaking today is Cheon Jong Beom.

102
00:11:01,930 --> 00:11:04,500
It's oddly different.

103
00:11:04,500 --> 00:11:08,380
Your feelings are still alive.

104
00:11:08,380 --> 00:11:10,250
Yeah?

105
00:11:22,640 --> 00:11:27,020
What could the secret of the real killer you missed in the book be?

106
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:33,250
While Gong In Woo killed, Gong Ji Cheol gathered up victims' belongings that could prove their identities.

107
00:11:33,250 --> 00:11:35,120
Among them, there's something that belonged to your stepfather, too.

108
00:11:35,120 --> 00:11:37,790
 (ID card for Gu Sang Gu) 

109
00:11:45,870 --> 00:11:50,200
I'm going to ask two questions right now. Give me answers that I can understand.

110
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:55,910
First, who sent the thugs to Gong Ji Cheol at Wonnam Hospital to kill him?

111
00:11:57,570 --> 00:12:00,090
Who do you think?

112
00:12:00,090 --> 00:12:03,420
It was the prosecutor in charge of Gong Ji Cheol's execution.

113
00:12:03,420 --> 00:12:06,080
Cheon Seok Tae?

114
00:12:06,080 --> 00:12:08,210
It's your father.

115
00:12:10,560 --> 00:12:15,170
Second, Baek Sang Ah calls me her friend.

116
00:12:15,170 --> 00:12:19,910
She said you've been watching me since I was born.

117
00:12:19,910 --> 00:12:22,320
What does it mean?

118
00:12:22,320 --> 00:12:25,950
Sang Ah?  Sang Ah, how did she...

119
00:12:25,950 --> 00:12:27,750
Your answer.

120
00:12:31,660 --> 00:12:34,520
The person who designed your DNA...

121
00:12:34,520 --> 00:12:39,040
it wasn't your mom, it was me.

122
00:12:39,040 --> 00:12:44,240
At Inseong Foundation's fertility clinic,

123
00:12:45,100 --> 00:12:48,800
I once switched some donated sperm.

124
00:12:50,150 --> 00:12:52,690
Your biological father

125
00:12:54,370 --> 00:12:57,660
wasn't a top 1% genius in Korea.

126
00:12:58,720 --> 00:13:02,890
I don't know who it was.

127
00:13:02,890 --> 00:13:06,260
It was donated to the hospital anonymously.

128
00:13:07,830 --> 00:13:10,410
Why did you...

129
00:13:10,410 --> 00:13:12,260
do that to me?

130
00:13:12,260 --> 00:13:19,070
At first, I wanted to place something foreign in Cheon Seok Tae's life.

131
00:13:19,900 --> 00:13:23,650
Since we're very ill-fated.

132
00:13:23,650 --> 00:13:27,240
I saw you for the first time when you were 13.

133
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:32,320
That day, I recognized right away that you were not an ordinary person.

134
00:13:33,820 --> 00:13:37,150
So I only wanted to watch you from afar.

135
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:48,300
Writer Jang Hye Mi, a bundle of lies. I want to reveal that to the world.

136
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:55,410
I guess you want to prove Gong Ji Cheol's innocence,

137
00:13:55,410 --> 00:14:00,720
but remember, I'm the only one in the world who can prove

138
00:14:00,720 --> 00:14:04,430
you were wrongly accused 32 years ago.

139
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:08,630
Now it's become very clear what we need from each other.

140
00:14:08,630 --> 00:14:15,220
How Prosecutor Cheon made Gong Ji Cheol into an uncommon serial killer,

141
00:14:15,220 --> 00:14:18,790
bring the evidence to me.

142
00:14:18,790 --> 00:14:23,970
You... had so much evidence.

143
00:14:23,970 --> 00:14:28,020
Why didn't you show it to Prosecutor Cheon 32 years ago?

144
00:14:28,020 --> 00:14:30,770
Would that have changed anything?

145
00:14:30,770 --> 00:14:35,230
He probably would have assumed it was trophies I collected from the murders.

146
00:14:35,230 --> 00:14:41,730
You also knew Gong In Woo was the murderer, but nothing changed.

147
00:14:41,730 --> 00:14:44,630
Since I was expendable.

148
00:14:48,550 --> 00:14:52,620
Heathcliff's revenge when he returned was because of love.

149
00:14:54,980 --> 00:14:57,480
Is it because of love for you, too?

150
00:15:53,730 --> 00:15:56,580
You did it while eating like this.

151
00:15:57,570 --> 00:16:02,520
Do you remember stabbing me with the scissors while I ate?

152
00:16:02,520 --> 00:16:04,640
Who are you?

153
00:16:04,640 --> 00:16:05,910
Why did you do that?

154
00:16:05,910 --> 00:16:08,950
I asked who you are.

155
00:16:08,950 --> 00:16:11,350
Your son, Gong Ji Cheol.

156
00:16:11,350 --> 00:16:13,350
What?

157
00:16:14,970 --> 00:16:17,720
How could you say something like that?

158
00:16:17,720 --> 00:16:21,050
Every time I got stabbed in the eye, I thought,

159
00:16:22,140 --> 00:16:26,020
"I really hope Mom's anger subsides quickly today.

160
00:16:26,730 --> 00:16:29,130
Let's just put up with it a little longer.

161
00:16:31,220 --> 00:16:33,730
If I put up with it a little more,

162
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:38,440
Mom will be nice to me today."

163
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:44,720
But I realized once I got stabbed in the eye.

164
00:16:46,060 --> 00:16:49,000
To you, I wasn't a human being,

165
00:16:50,260 --> 00:16:52,370
I was an object.

166
00:16:53,400 --> 00:16:56,760
A very dirty object that didn't matter

167
00:16:59,260 --> 00:17:01,950
if it died and got chucked in the trash.

168
00:17:01,950 --> 00:17:08,130
Are you... really Ji Cheol?

169
00:17:08,130 --> 00:17:11,120
I thought I should live no matter what.

170
00:17:12,880 --> 00:17:19,810
The only means of getting revenge on you was for me to stay alive and become an adult

171
00:17:19,810 --> 00:17:22,460
and for you to get old.

172
00:17:30,690 --> 00:17:36,430
But... even meeting like this...

173
00:17:38,020 --> 00:17:40,560
I can't get revenge on you.

174
00:19:13,990 --> 00:19:16,520
   

175
00:19:17,890 --> 00:19:20,560
 Do you want to have a party as a family? 

176
00:19:28,700 --> 00:19:33,200
Our Jong Beom has become a real man since I last saw him!

177
00:19:33,200 --> 00:19:36,860
Listen, Jong Beom, it's Sa Bin's birthday soon.

178
00:19:36,860 --> 00:19:38,520
Let's go on a family vacation together.

179
00:19:38,520 --> 00:19:42,200
Your face just begs for my affection.

180
00:19:42,200 --> 00:19:44,270
Why don't you just be our nephew-in-law?

181
00:19:45,680 --> 00:19:49,060
Uncle, let's not cross the line.

182
00:19:49,060 --> 00:19:53,610
It's not the DMZ. What line can you not cross as a man and a woman?

183
00:19:53,610 --> 00:19:54,610
Never you mind!

184
00:19:54,610 --> 00:19:59,210
Jong Beom, tell me. You like Sa Bin, don't you?

185
00:19:59,210 --> 00:20:03,770
I can tell by looking at your eyes! I'm a pro!

186
00:20:03,770 --> 00:20:05,460
Uncle, come on!

187
00:20:05,460 --> 00:20:08,780
Yes, I like her.

188
00:20:13,770 --> 00:20:16,350
Sa Bin, how do you feel?

189
00:20:16,350 --> 00:20:18,550
We like each other as teacher and student.

190
00:20:18,550 --> 00:20:21,430
Isn't that a given? He's my favorite pupil.

191
00:20:21,430 --> 00:20:26,040
Sa Bin, when you see him, is he cool or pitiful?

192
00:20:26,040 --> 00:20:28,630
When a woman really loves a man,

193
00:20:28,630 --> 00:20:31,820
she feels pity for him, that's what I heard.

194
00:20:31,820 --> 00:20:34,580
Like a mom, you want to comfort him and embrace him.

195
00:20:34,580 --> 00:20:37,390
If people say anything to him, you want to fight them off.

196
00:20:37,390 --> 00:20:42,230
That's real, real love.

197
00:20:42,230 --> 00:20:47,400
Is that so? If you know so much, why are you still single?

198
00:20:47,400 --> 00:20:49,650
There's not even one woman

199
00:20:49,650 --> 00:20:55,490
who pities me! It's my fate to be lonely.

200
00:20:55,490 --> 00:20:57,210
You're the same.

201
00:20:57,210 --> 00:20:59,660
This little weasel!

202
00:20:59,660 --> 00:21:04,100
Fine! Let's die together so that you and I won't be lonely!

203
00:21:04,100 --> 00:21:06,870
I'll warmly embrace you in my arms!

204
00:21:06,870 --> 00:21:12,100
♫   Because you were the first to come close   ♫

205
00:21:14,060 --> 00:21:16,680
♫   Even if it's a love I can't fulfill   ♫

206
00:21:16,680 --> 00:21:19,580
 I like you. I like you, 

207
00:21:19,580 --> 00:21:21,700
 so you can never get hurt. 

208
00:21:21,700 --> 00:21:26,620
 To be honest, since the first time I saw you, my heart raced. 

209
00:21:26,620 --> 00:21:30,050
♫   I can't   ♫

210
00:21:30,050 --> 00:21:35,600
♫   Even though I know you can't come to me   ♫

211
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:38,100
 Can I ask why you shot me? 

212
00:21:38,100 --> 00:21:40,120
 Because you tried to kill Jeong Sa Bin. 

213
00:21:40,120 --> 00:21:42,670
 Are you still suspecting Jong Beom? 

214
00:21:42,670 --> 00:21:47,500
 As much you like Jeong Sa Bin, Baek Sang Ah will want to kill her. 

215
00:21:47,500 --> 00:21:50,120
♫   Even while exhausted   ♫

216
00:21:50,120 --> 00:21:54,220
♫   I say that I'm fine   ♫

217
00:21:55,100 --> 00:22:01,320
♫   Even though it hurts, this is not goodbye   ♫

218
00:22:02,630 --> 00:22:04,510
When is your birthday?

219
00:22:04,510 --> 00:22:07,520
Me? May 31st.

220
00:22:07,520 --> 00:22:13,240
The day my father carried out his first execution, I was born. Isn't it unique?

221
00:22:13,240 --> 00:22:19,950
So the person I can't forgive as long as I live is that convict, Gong Ji Cheol.

222
00:22:20,780 --> 00:22:25,740
You haven't seen the face of the convict whose remains we reconstructed, have you?

223
00:22:29,590 --> 00:22:33,600
I think he looks like you.

224
00:22:35,530 --> 00:22:37,850
In what way?

225
00:22:39,780 --> 00:22:43,670
He looks lonely. It hurts me.

226
00:22:44,730 --> 00:22:45,980
I'm really...

227
00:22:45,980 --> 00:22:48,620
It's an illness. Being excessively absorbed in the remains.

228
00:22:48,620 --> 00:22:51,320
You don't need to have sympathy.

229
00:22:51,320 --> 00:22:57,540
His bones were broken everywhere, his eyes were stabbed, and he was nutritionally deficient.

230
00:22:57,540 --> 00:23:02,320
His scars were mostly from when he was young.

231
00:23:04,010 --> 00:23:10,800
If he had been loved, he could have lived another kind of life.

232
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:12,810
I don't think so.

233
00:23:13,760 --> 00:23:19,110
The relationship formed with that convict would have been completely ill-fated.

234
00:23:19,110 --> 00:23:23,800
It might not have been an ill-fated relationship, just a fated one.

235
00:23:23,800 --> 00:23:28,450
Maybe he became a convict because he didn't get to form those relationships sooner.

236
00:23:29,200 --> 00:23:32,900
Had the relationship come sooner, he might not

237
00:23:32,900 --> 00:23:35,810
have lived like that and died that way.

238
00:23:45,540 --> 00:23:46,940
Yes, Prosecutor Kim.

239
00:23:46,940 --> 00:23:51,230
 Can I see you for a bit? 

240
00:23:51,230 --> 00:23:55,210
What's wrong with your voice? Is something wrong?

241
00:23:57,330 --> 00:23:59,640
Okay, I'll do that.

242
00:24:00,590 --> 00:24:04,180
Sorry, Prosecutor Kim needs to talk to me.

243
00:24:04,180 --> 00:24:06,500
Go ahead, I'll wait.

244
00:24:06,500 --> 00:24:10,230
Here? You don't know how long it'll take.

245
00:24:10,230 --> 00:24:11,410
I'll wait.

246
00:24:11,410 --> 00:24:13,990
You're not even well. Go inside.

247
00:24:19,790 --> 00:24:22,970
 Jeong Ha Eun, how long... 

248
00:24:22,970 --> 00:24:25,760
 can you wait for me? 

